178
00:11:40,034 --> 00:11:42,403
[chuckles, exhales]

179
00:11:47,274 --> 00:11:50,344
Easy. Easy, easy, easy.

180
00:11:50,377 --> 00:11:52,079
Easy.

181
00:11:52,112 --> 00:11:53,147
What the...

182
00:11:56,518 --> 00:11:57,751
A fucking pipe bomb?

183
00:11:57,785 --> 00:11:59,119
[exhales]

184
00:12:02,089 --> 00:12:04,526
Get that out of here right now.

185
00:12:04,559 --> 00:12:06,927
If we need a distraction,
we could use it.

186
00:12:06,961 --> 00:12:09,964
Then we'll have Homeland Security
on your asses for, like, the end of time.

187
00:12:09,997 --> 00:12:11,165
You built this?

188
00:12:11,198 --> 00:12:12,499
From scratch, bro.

189
00:12:12,534 --> 00:12:14,168
That guy from YouTube,

190
00:12:14,201 --> 00:12:16,103
he could teach a toddler
to make one of these things.

191
00:12:16,136 --> 00:12:17,171
That's terrifying.

192
00:12:17,204 --> 00:12:18,806
[Casey] Yeah.

193
00:12:18,839 --> 00:12:20,841
Yeah, it kind of is terrifying.

194
00:12:20,874 --> 00:12:23,244
Whoa. You want me
to get rid of it?

195
00:12:23,277 --> 00:12:26,413
Yes! Obviously. I can't even
believe this is a real conversation.

196
00:12:26,447 --> 00:12:31,051
Let's stash it, you know,
for an emergency.

197
00:12:31,085 --> 00:12:33,254
You're both insane.
I'm just thinking ahead.

198
00:12:33,287 --> 00:12:35,889
Like Cap taught me, right, Case?

199
00:12:35,923 --> 00:12:37,825
[chuckles]
[hands slap]

200
00:12:38,892 --> 00:12:40,894
Okay, goodbye.

201
00:12:40,928 --> 00:12:43,197
[Mike] Come on. You're a little bit
impressed. Where are you going?

202
00:12:44,431 --> 00:12:45,567
