Sykes.

203
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:47,569
Wait, wait, wait, Sykes.

204
00:12:47,602 --> 00:12:49,504
I'm having a little
get-together tomorrow night.

205
00:12:49,537 --> 00:12:52,373
Couple of people. If you
wanna come by, just come by.

206
00:12:53,274 --> 00:12:54,375
Maybe.

207
00:12:55,175 --> 00:12:56,210
Bye.

208
00:12:57,845 --> 00:12:59,079
What's her deal?

209
00:13:00,615 --> 00:13:01,915
Bye, Sykes.

210
00:13:01,949 --> 00:13:02,950
Bye!

211
00:13:03,984 --> 00:13:05,185
She's right, you know?

212
00:13:06,220 --> 00:13:07,821
You are insane.

213
00:13:09,056 --> 00:13:10,357
No, but I love it.

214
00:13:12,226 --> 00:13:13,327
My man.

215
00:13:14,061 --> 00:13:15,530
[clears throat]

216
00:13:15,563 --> 00:13:17,364
[exhales] Now...

217
00:13:18,132 --> 00:13:21,302
[Casey chuckles]
How'd you do this?

218
00:13:21,335 --> 00:13:23,070
[chuckles]
I'm actually glad you asked.

219
00:13:25,507 --> 00:13:26,940
[glasses clinking]

220
00:13:27,509 --> 00:13:28,543
[chuckles]

221
00:13:33,180 --> 00:13:34,481
How do you do that?

222
00:13:36,383 --> 00:13:38,118
Lots of practice.

223
00:13:38,152 --> 00:13:40,854
How can you be
at the wrong place

224
00:13:40,888 --> 00:13:43,324
at the right time all the time?

225
00:13:44,058 --> 00:13:46,561
These guys were spraying
and praying.

226
00:13:46,594 --> 00:13:49,229
<i>It was 50/50 that they would
have hit you or Fitz.</i>

227
00:13:49,263 --> 00:13:52,099
One day, your luck is going
to run out, cowboy.

228
00:13:53,934 --> 00:13:55,869
I should have done it alone.

229
00:13:55,903 --> 00:13:57,338
[exhales]
He'll pull through.

230
00:13:58,472 --> 00:14:03,110
Listen,
we are outgunned, outpaced.

231
00:14:03,143 --> 00:14:07,281
The only way to catch
this crew is in the act.

232
00:14:07,314 --> 00:14:09,517
You got a theory?
Yeah.

233
00:14:10,484 --> 00:14:12,953
Those guys are smart, trained.

234
00:14:12,986 --> 00:14:16,223
I mean, all they stole
is just a bit of cash

235
00:14:16,256 --> 00:14:19,594
