of baseball training cards.

236
00:14:19,627 --> 00:14:22,329
Smart people don't rob banks.

237
00:14:22,363 --> 00:14:24,566
Yeah, true that.

238
00:14:24,599 --> 00:14:27,434
This crew is tight.
And they move like a team.

239
00:14:27,468 --> 00:14:29,203
Hmm.

240
00:14:29,236 --> 00:14:30,270
Yeah, but...

241
00:14:30,304 --> 00:14:32,272
Athletes.

242
00:14:32,306 --> 00:14:35,309
<i>The guard said he got
truck stick trying to escape.</i>

243
00:14:36,611 --> 00:14:38,312
That tracks.

244
00:14:38,345 --> 00:14:40,981
You know,
the rest of the team think

245
00:14:41,014 --> 00:14:43,417
that I'm crazier than you
for thinking like this,

246
00:14:43,450 --> 00:14:44,686
but hear me out.

247
00:14:44,719 --> 00:14:46,387
Those guys are not from here.

248
00:14:47,555 --> 00:14:51,258
One of the witnesses said that
they speak with a New York accent.

249
00:14:51,291 --> 00:14:52,426
So?

250
00:14:52,459 --> 00:14:54,596
Have you heard
of phantom planes?

251
00:14:54,629 --> 00:14:56,063
The Phantom?

252
00:14:56,096 --> 00:14:59,400
The one in the purple suit
