die. For real. Fuck off.

503
00:27:16,170 --> 00:27:17,905
No. One-of-a-kind
collector's item

504
00:27:17,938 --> 00:27:20,107
that sells at an auction.

505
00:27:20,141 --> 00:27:23,677
Guys, um, we do this job, right?

506
00:27:23,711 --> 00:27:26,380
We're gonna have a nice
little deposit for our pensions.

507
00:27:28,716 --> 00:27:31,285
Come on. I've seen it.
I got it all in my head.

508
00:27:31,318 --> 00:27:33,387
I know all the angles.
We can do this.

509
00:27:36,056 --> 00:27:38,058
I'm gonna pass
unless I have my team.

510
00:27:38,959 --> 00:27:40,394
What about Mercer?

511
00:27:40,427 --> 00:27:42,763
Fuck Mercer, okay?

512
00:27:42,796 --> 00:27:45,900
I got one fucking cowboy right
here. I don't know about Mercer.

513
00:27:48,068 --> 00:27:49,470
Fine.
I'm in.

514
00:27:49,504 --> 00:27:51,906
Let's go steal Wayne
Gretzky. Have a salami.

515
00:27:51,939 --> 00:27:53,240
Fuck you.
Fuck off.

516
00:27:53,274 --> 00:27:55,109
[exhales] You couldn't
afford a heater?

517
00:27:55,142 --> 00:27:56,343
[chuckles]

518
00:27:58,445 --> 00:28:02,917
[instructor] Every move should
improve your position or hurt the enemy.

519
00:28:02,950 --> 00:28:06,053
This is a battlefield. And
never forget why you're fighting.

520
00:28:07,922 --> 00:28:09,423
Now, the knight.

521
00:28:09,456 --> 00:28:11,759
The knight is the most
dangerous piece on the board.

522
00:28:12,693 --> 00:28:15,296
The knight can strike
when you least expect it.

523
00:28:17,264 --> 00:28:20,134
The knight moves in ways
most people won't understand.

524
00:28:21,068 --> 00:28:23,938
[phone ringing]

525
00:28:27,074 --> 00:28:30,411
Now, what the hell? How the fuck
did you... Where the fuck is my security?

526
00:28:30,444 --> 00:28:31,845
Where's Brigga?

527
00:28:31,879 --> 00:28:34,014
I hope I'm not, uh,
interrupting.

528
00:28:34,048 --> 00:28:37,151
Detective, you're a long way
from home, you know that?

529
00:28:37,184 --> 00:28:39,286
- Who are you?
- San go.

530
00:28:39,320 --> 00:28:40,921
Oh, gesundheit.

531
00:28:40,955 --> 00:28:43,490
Welcome to my humble fortress.

532
00:28:43,525 --> 00:28:46,160
Nice place for a bookie.
[Winna] Thanks.

533
00:28:46,193 --> 00:28:48,362
Yeah, we say if there's
a sport with a winner,

534
00:28:48,395 --> 00:28:50,965
then there's also a loser
that was willing to bet on it.

535
00:28:50,998 --> 00:28:53,367
- We need a word.
- You need a word? I got a word.

536
00:28:53,400 --> 00:28:54,401
"Lawyer."

537
00:28:54,435 --> 00:28:55,936
Lawyer?

538
00:28:55,970 --> 00:28:58,506
I got four more words.
"Speak to my lawyer."

539
00:28:58,540 --> 00:29:01,475
As you can see, I'm in
the middle of a lesson here.

540
00:29:01,509 --> 00:29:06,548
Do you know who this is? This is
the youngest chess master in history.

541
00:29:06,581 --> 00:29:08,048
[Knight] Well, good for him.

542
00:29:08,082 --> 00:29:11,085
Hey, this is my home.
All right?

543
00:29:11,118 --> 00:29:12,186
Show some respect.

544
00:29:12,219 --> 00:29:14,288
I apologize for these clowns.

545
00:29:14,321 --> 00:29:18,058
Hey, kid, go learn a real sport.

546
00:29:20,160 --> 00:29:21,362
Sit.

547
00:29:24,265 --> 00:29:26,400
Now, detectives, talk to me.

548
00:29:27,167 --> 00:29:28,435
What can I do you for?

549
00:29:28,469 --> 00:29:30,838
We know all about you, Winna.

550
00:29:30,871 --> 00:29:33,307
Kicked out of Goldman Sachs
for insider trading.

551
00:29:33,340 --> 00:29:36,176
Got a sweetheart deal
with the judge.

552
00:29:36,210 --> 00:29:40,080
You were a CI
for the local PD and feds.

553
00:29:40,114 --> 00:29:42,983
Oh, so you found
my Wikipedia page, did you?

554
00:29:43,017 --> 00:29:46,453
And I'm glad to see the government's
finally hiring guys who can read.

555
00:29:46,487 --> 00:29:50,024
So tell me, if I turn
your pockets inside out,

556
00:29:50,057 --> 00:29:51,258
what am I going to find?

557
00:29:51,292 --> 00:29:53,360
I don't know.
What will you find?

558
00:29:54,461 --> 00:29:56,964
Perhaps a lawsuit for
breaching my civil liberties?

559
00:29:56,997 --> 00:29:58,365
Really?
Yeah.

560
00:29:58,399 --> 00:30:00,301
[Knight]
You know a lot of ex-pros.

561
00:30:00,334 --> 00:30:02,002
Make some scratch.

562
00:30:02,036 --> 00:30:03,904
Yep.

563
00:30:03,937 --> 00:30:05,973
[San go exhales] I'd like a
couple of them for a messy job.

564
00:30:06,006 --> 00:30:08,342
A messy drug job.

565
00:30:08,375 --> 00:30:11,078
You know anything
about that? No.

566
00:30:11,111 --> 00:30:12,880
Not to the best
of my recollection.

567
00:30:13,515 --> 00:30:14,815
Think real hard.

568
00:30:15,449 --> 00:30:17,017
And what's in it for me?

569
00:30:17,051 --> 00:30:18,986
Christmas dinner at my place.

570
00:30:19,019 --> 00:30:20,154
Oh, yeah?

571
00:30:21,088 --> 00:30:22,289
I think I'll pass.

572
00:30:22,323 --> 00:30:25,092
Well, better
than the alternative.

573
00:30:25,125 --> 00:30:26,528
And what's that?

574
00:30:26,561 --> 00:30:28,996
You have dinner at his.

575
00:30:31,131 --> 00:30:32,600
You know, call ahead next time.

576
00:30:32,634 --> 00:30:35,002
I'll make sure
the gates are locked.

577
00:30:35,035 --> 00:30:39,006
If you're covering for them,
I'll find out.

578
00:30:41,108 --> 00:30:42,876
Now, is that a threat,
Detective?

579
00:30:44,978 --> 00:30:46,914
Got a lot of property here.

580
00:30:48,315 --> 00:30:53,053
Lot of places
to get lost, disappear.

581
00:30:55,189 --> 00:30:56,490
Lot of places.

582
00:30:59,360 --> 00:31:00,494
We're done.

583
00:31:01,629 --> 00:31:02,930
Get out.

584
00:31:23,551 --> 00:31:25,319
[San go exhales]

585
00:31:29,957 --> 00:31:31,125
[Knight] Wait here.

586
00:31:42,637 --> 00:31:44,672
What the fuck
are you doing here?

587
00:31:45,472 --> 00:31:46,940
What do you got?

588
00:31:49,143 --> 00:31:50,177
What do I got?

589
00:31:52,614 --> 00:31:54,982
What about the truck heist?

590
00:31:55,015 --> 00:31:58,285
I don't know anything about it,
but if I did know something about it...

591
00:32:00,254 --> 00:32:01,422
I would look at Casey Rhodes.

592
00:32:01,455 --> 00:32:03,056
Casey Rhodes?

593
00:32:03,090 --> 00:32:04,626
Yeah, look to him.

594
00:32:06,093 --> 00:32:07,595
[laughs]

595
00:32:07,629 --> 00:32:10,197
Yeah, where can I find him?

596
00:32:10,230 --> 00:32:12,499
I'm not gonna do your
fucking job for you, buddy.

597
00:32:12,534 --> 00:32:15,335
And I shouldn't have to explain
why this can't come back to Winna.

598
00:32:15,369 --> 00:32:17,004
- [phone ringing]
- [Brigga] <i>Don't forget.</i>

599
00:32:17,037 --> 00:32:18,506
You still owe him.

600
00:32:18,540 --> 00:32:21,308
[ringing continues]
Is that a fact?

601
00:32:22,644 --> 00:32:25,112
[ringing stops]
Yeah. It's a fact.

602
00:32:25,145 --> 00:32:27,080
Now get the fuck outta here.

603
00:32:43,798 --> 00:32:45,265
Yo, you got my stuff?
Yeah.

604
00:32:45,299 --> 00:32:46,333
Yeah.

605
00:32:46,366 --> 00:32:48,202
Any news on the next one?

606
00:32:48,235 --> 00:32:50,705
Uh, nothing yet.
I'll let you know.

607
00:32:54,141 --> 00:32:56,009
No serial numbers.
Complete virgin.

608
00:32:56,811 --> 00:32:59,547
Not for long.
Yes.

609
00:32:59,581 --> 00:33:01,616
All right. Let's get the fuck
outta here, yeah? Sure.

610
00:33:01,649 --> 00:33:03,350
[San go] Casey Rhodes.

611
00:33:05,352 --> 00:33:07,354
- Give that to...
- I'm not going back to jail, man.

612
00:33:07,387 --> 00:33:09,223
You're not gonna...
If they had anything on us...

613
00:33:09,256 --> 00:33:10,725
Lose it behind
your fucking back.

614
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:14,729
[Mercer] Can I help you?

615
00:33:14,762 --> 00:33:16,330
[San go] Can I see some ID?

616
00:33:18,065 --> 00:33:20,033
You know,
I think I left it at home.

617
00:33:20,067 --> 00:33:22,336
What about you? Do you,
uh... Do you have your ID?

618
00:33:22,369 --> 00:33:25,138
Yeah, I think
I left mine at home too.

619
00:33:25,172 --> 00:33:26,373
I know who you are.

620
00:33:27,274 --> 00:33:29,476
Casey Rhodes.
And?

621
00:33:29,511 --> 00:33:31,411
Rookie of the year.

622
00:33:32,279 --> 00:33:34,147
Drafted by the Chargers.

623
00:33:34,949 --> 00:33:36,718
That's a really good memory,
pops.

624
00:33:38,085 --> 00:33:39,721
Numbers are good?

625
00:33:39,754 --> 00:33:41,288
[Knight] Astronomical.

626
00:33:41,321 --> 00:33:43,156
The next Tom Brady.

627
00:33:43,858 --> 00:33:47,060
Lost a lot of money.
Went bankrupt.

628
00:33:47,094 --> 00:33:48,730
[San go]
Oh, I've heard about you.

629
00:33:48,763 --> 00:33:51,064
Didn't you get banned
for shaving points?

630
00:33:51,098 --> 00:33:52,534
Yeah, you want
a fuckin' autograph?

631
00:33:55,269 --> 00:33:56,804
Get in the fucking car.
Let's go.

632
00:33:57,739 --> 00:33:59,273
- Knight.
- [gunfire]

633
00:33:59,306 --> 00:34:01,241
[tires screeching]

634
00:34:03,343 --> 00:34:04,712
[Fitz] <i>Knight, help me.</i>

635
00:34:07,414 --> 00:34:08,683
[phone ringing]

636
00:34:08,716 --> 00:34:10,417
Yeah, you want
a fuckin' autograph?

637
00:34:12,219 --> 00:34:14,488
[San go] Knight, you okay?

638
00:34:14,522 --> 00:34:17,257
[ringing stops]

639
00:34:17,291 --> 00:34:20,562
I was talking about you,
not to you.

640
00:34:20,595 --> 00:34:23,230
[San go] Okay, now we have
a mutual friend. Winna.

641
00:34:23,263 --> 00:34:24,364
Uh, Winna.

642
00:34:24,398 --> 00:34:26,466
Hmm. You guys...
You know Winna?

643
00:34:26,501 --> 00:34:28,268
It's a small world.

644
00:34:28,302 --> 00:34:31,405
Maybe we could all grab some
brunch or something sometime.

645
00:34:31,438 --> 00:34:33,273
Really nice.

646
00:34:33,307 --> 00:34:35,543
[San go] That's real cute.
What's your current address?

647
00:34:36,176 --> 00:34:37,344
Me?

648
00:34:37,377 --> 00:34:39,413
Uh, you got a pen?

649
00:34:39,446 --> 00:34:41,683
Okay. It's, uh,
just on the corner

650
00:34:41,716 --> 00:34:44,418
of, uh, "Speak to my"
and "Fuckin' lawyer."

651
00:34:44,451 --> 00:34:46,453
[Casey laughs]
[Mercer] It's a new suburb.

652
00:34:46,486 --> 00:34:48,856
You're friends
with Winna, obviously.

653
00:34:48,890 --> 00:34:51,258
He must train his dogs
really well.

654
00:34:51,291 --> 00:34:52,760
Woof.

655
00:34:52,794 --> 00:34:56,229
Stay safe out there.
Be seeing you.

656
00:34:57,331 --> 00:34:58,666
You too.

657
00:35:11,846 --> 00:35:13,615
[radio chatter]

658
00:35:13,648 --> 00:35:15,550
[phone rings in distance]

659
00:35:19,687 --> 00:35:20,855
Captain. Captain Shea.

660
00:35:21,723 --> 00:35:23,390
Detective San go.
Mmm.

661
00:35:23,423 --> 00:35:25,425
Thanks for taking the time.
Where's your partner?

662
00:35:25,459 --> 00:35:26,928
He's not my partner.

663
00:35:26,961 --> 00:35:28,763
What can I do for you,
Detective?

664
00:35:28,796 --> 00:35:31,532
We're here as a gesture
of goodwill.

665
00:35:31,566 --> 00:35:33,801
I was wondering if we
could share information.

666
00:35:33,835 --> 00:35:35,670
You're out of your jurisdiction.

667
00:35:36,904 --> 00:35:42,309
Captain, we have a cop who
is right now fighting for his life.

668
00:35:43,911 --> 00:35:47,649
Detective Knight had some leads
regarding some old friend of his.

669
00:35:47,682 --> 00:35:49,349
Andrew Winna.

670
00:35:50,250 --> 00:35:51,819
Old friend?

671
00:35:51,853 --> 00:35:54,221
Yeah, he might have
been a bookie or CI.

672
00:35:54,254 --> 00:35:56,758
Just an old friend of Knight.

673
00:35:56,791 --> 00:35:59,326
Does he know him
or "he knew him"?

674
00:36:01,294 --> 00:36:04,264
Knight might be
rough around the edges,

675
00:36:04,297 --> 00:36:05,767
but he's a good cop.

676
00:36:05,800 --> 00:36:07,200
Mm-hmm.

677
00:36:07,234 --> 00:36:08,468
Got anything concrete?

678
00:36:09,570 --> 00:36:12,239
Winna's head of security,
Brigga.

679
00:36:12,272 --> 00:36:14,241
He played football
with Casey Rhodes.

680
00:36:14,274 --> 00:36:15,743
I guess they had a falling out,

681
00:36:15,777 --> 00:36:18,646
because he implicated Casey
and his crew in the heist.

682
00:36:18,680 --> 00:36:20,882
They cover their tracks
very well.

683
00:36:20,915 --> 00:36:23,551
Hit the target
and disappear like ghosts.

684
00:36:23,584 --> 00:36:25,853
Look, Detective,
I know your captain.

685
00:36:25,887 --> 00:36:28,255
She vouched for you,
but not your partner.

686
00:36:28,288 --> 00:36:29,624
She sent me his file.

687
00:36:29,657 --> 00:36:32,392
It is the opinion
of the department

688
00:36:32,426 --> 00:36:34,662
that if James Knight
wasn't hunting bank robbers,

689
00:36:34,696 --> 00:36:36,496
he'd be robbing banks.

690
00:36:37,065 --> 00:36:38,966
He's a thug with a badge.

691
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:40,868
If they strike again,
I'll give you clearance.

692
00:36:40,902 --> 00:36:42,837
But stay out of our way.

693
00:36:42,870 --> 00:36:44,639
Welcome to New York, Detective.

694
00:36:44,672 --> 00:36:48,341
Have fun being a
tourist in my city. Mmm.

695
00:36:49,544 --> 00:36:50,778
[sniffs]

696
00:36:51,946 --> 00:36:52,980
[sighs]

697
00:36:54,347 --> 00:36:56,383
[dog barking in distance]

698
00:36:57,317 --> 00:36:58,753
[crowd noise on TV]

699
00:37:02,023 --> 00:37:04,692
That was in! Get the fuck
out of the way. That was in!

700
00:37:04,726 --> 00:37:06,861
What are you, blind?
Who the fuck is that ref, huh?

701
00:37:06,894 --> 00:37:09,864
He's a dead man,
that's who he is.

702
00:37:09,897 --> 00:37:13,400
You guys are good at what you do, all
right? You both work for me now, okay?

703
00:37:13,433 --> 00:37:15,737
25%, your take. No cutting
or I take it out in blood.

704
00:37:15,770 --> 00:37:17,839
I'm kidding, but not really.

705
00:37:19,974 --> 00:37:21,509
What?

706
00:37:21,542 --> 00:37:23,611
It's Knight.
What the fuck does he want?

707
00:37:25,713 --> 00:37:27,280
Give me that phone.

708
00:37:28,448 --> 00:37:31,284
What the fuck are you doing?

709
00:37:31,318 --> 00:37:33,554
Why are you rolling on me
with that jamoke, huh?

710
00:37:33,588 --> 00:37:35,355
We have an understanding,
Detective.

711
00:37:35,388 --> 00:37:37,625
<i>Stay away, or else.</i>

712
00:37:37,658 --> 00:37:39,426
[Knight]
<i>They got him on life support.</i>

713
00:37:39,459 --> 00:37:42,730
Oh, okay. Well, hazard of the
job. Send him some flowers.

714
00:37:42,764 --> 00:37:44,397
Who shot him?

715
00:37:44,431 --> 00:37:46,366
<i>How the fuck would I know
who shot some guy</i>

716
00:37:46,399 --> 00:37:47,502
<i>in your dirty little city?</i>

717
00:37:47,969 --> 00:37:49,604
<i>We spoke to him.</i>

718
00:37:49,637 --> 00:37:52,372
Yeah, Casey Rhodes.
And his buddy.

719
00:37:54,675 --> 00:37:56,677
They're both stand-up guys.

720
00:37:56,711 --> 00:37:59,346
We both agreed not to ask questions
that we don't want answers to.

721
00:37:59,379 --> 00:38:01,516
<i>If I get the evidence
that Rhodes shot Fitz...</i>

722
00:38:01,549 --> 00:38:04,852
Uh-uh. Watch that tone,
Detective.

723
00:38:04,886 --> 00:38:07,755
<i>I could always call IA and let
them know about our little chat.</i>

724
00:38:07,789 --> 00:38:10,558
<i>We threatening
each other now?</i> No.

725
00:38:10,591 --> 00:38:13,594
No, we are not.
Now, listen to me.

726
00:38:13,628 --> 00:38:17,565
Back off from Rhodes and Mercer.

727
00:38:17,598 --> 00:38:19,767
<i>If I find out you had
anything to do with this...</i>

728
00:38:19,801 --> 00:38:22,804
Oh, so much plot and excitement.

729
00:38:22,837 --> 00:38:24,906
Listen to me. No more
empty threats, Detective.

730
00:38:24,939 --> 00:38:26,974
I can take you out
whenever I want,

731
00:38:27,008 --> 00:38:29,010
<i>wherever I want, okay?</i>

732
00:38:29,043 --> 00:38:32,046
If you don't believe me, I'd
love to give you a demonstration.

733
00:38:32,079 --> 00:38:34,015
Fitz is still in the ICU, right?

734
00:38:34,916 --> 00:38:36,416
One call from me,

735
00:38:36,449 --> 00:38:38,385
I'll have him moved
to the morgue. Bye.

736
00:38:39,954 --> 00:38:41,055
[scoffs]

737
00:38:41,722 --> 00:38:43,456
[Brigga laughs]

738
00:38:43,490 --> 00:38:45,458
[rain pattering]
[thunder rumbling]

739
00:38:47,460 --> 00:38:49,697
[vehicle approaching]

740
00:38:53,433 --> 00:38:54,467
[door opens]

741
00:38:54,502 --> 00:38:55,736
[Sykes] And the good news?

742
00:38:55,770 --> 00:38:58,739
[door closes]
Uh, you're late.

743
00:38:58,773 --> 00:39:02,375
How 'bout getting a fucking
watch? You find the blueprints?

744
00:39:02,409 --> 00:39:06,647
Yeah. But I did some digging
on those cops that paid you a visit.

745
00:39:08,149 --> 00:39:09,951
Anything good?

746
00:39:09,984 --> 00:39:14,889
Yeah. So first up, we have
Detective God win Frensaw San go.

747
00:39:14,922 --> 00:39:17,525
Analyst with the CIA
for seven years.

748
00:39:17,558 --> 00:39:21,095
He settled down in LA,
made detective in a year.

749
00:39:21,128 --> 00:39:23,396
In a year?
[Sykes] Yeah.

750
00:39:23,430 --> 00:39:26,667
That's good. What about
the other guy? The bald guy.

751
00:39:27,869 --> 00:39:28,903
The other bald one?

752
