00:54:33,608 --> 00:54:35,710
Let's go! Come on!

1002
00:54:35,743 --> 00:54:38,079
Let's go, buddy.
[engine starts]

1003
00:54:38,112 --> 00:54:40,782
We have to get out, for
fuck's sake. [tires screech]

1004
00:54:41,716 --> 00:54:43,785
[sirens wailing]

1005
00:54:43,818 --> 00:54:45,385
Fuck, fuck, fuck.

1006
00:54:45,418 --> 00:54:47,688
We needed Mercer.
Rather him than fucking Sykes!

1007
00:54:49,757 --> 00:54:51,793
[radio chatter]

1008
00:54:53,628 --> 00:54:54,929
[grunts]

1009
00:54:59,033 --> 00:55:00,535
[grunts]

1010
00:55:01,269 --> 00:55:04,071
Case, we have to
go back for her.

1011
00:55:04,105 --> 00:55:06,908
It's gonna be okay.
Just stick to the plan.

1012
00:55:06,941 --> 00:55:08,709
[panting]

1013
00:55:10,678 --> 00:55:12,079
Here you go.

1014
00:55:12,647 --> 00:55:14,515
Come on, come on, come on.

1015
00:55:25,392 --> 00:55:27,061
[engine starts]

1016
00:55:37,404 --> 00:55:38,706
[officer]
They wiped the counters.

1017
00:55:38,739 --> 00:55:40,407
There's fingerprints everywhere.

1018
00:55:40,440 --> 00:55:42,475
This is open and shut.

1019
00:55:42,510 --> 00:55:46,446
Yo, check it. We got fucking Dave
Chapelle and Patrick Stewart over here.

1020
00:55:46,479 --> 00:55:49,784
[officer 2] I can't believe the
captain's letting them tag along.

1021
00:55:49,817 --> 00:55:52,887
Watch your back. Yep.
There you go.

1022
00:55:54,522 --> 00:55:55,857
What was stolen?

1023
00:55:55,890 --> 00:55:59,794
Uh, some one-of-a-kind
sport card.

1024
00:55:59,827 --> 00:56:01,494
Some shit like that.

1025
00:56:01,529 --> 00:56:03,030
Sold at 2.2 million.

1026
00:56:03,064 --> 00:56:05,666
The woman we picked up
didn't say a word.

1027
00:56:06,300 --> 00:56:07,935
She didn't have it with her.

1028
00:56:07,969 --> 00:56:10,004
It must still be in here.

1029
00:56:10,037 --> 00:56:11,539
[Winna] Officers.

1030
00:56:12,974 --> 00:56:14,441
Hey.

1031
00:56:14,976 --> 00:56:16,777
I remember you.

1032
00:56:16,811 --> 00:56:20,548
- Some night, huh?
- Yeah, walk the scene.

1033
00:56:21,682 --> 00:56:23,150
Yeah, see what you see.

1034
00:56:26,187 --> 00:56:27,555
I love that guy.

1035
00:56:28,089 --> 00:56:29,757
If you're involved,

1036
00:56:30,258 --> 00:56:31,893
I won't cover for you.

1037
00:56:35,596 --> 00:56:37,565
I was just here
for the auction, sir.

1038
00:56:37,598 --> 00:56:38,833
[quietly] Shut up.

1039
00:56:40,501 --> 00:56:42,069
Nice badge.

1040
00:56:42,937 --> 00:56:44,005
Thanks.

1041
00:56:45,472 --> 00:56:48,910
However, my escort tonight
has already left,

1042
00:56:48,943 --> 00:56:51,712
so, uh,
I'm gonna need a new one.

1043
00:56:52,613 --> 00:56:53,881
That's where you come in.

1044
00:56:53,915 --> 00:56:55,549
So why don't you walk me out?

1045
00:56:57,852 --> 00:56:58,953
No.

1046
00:57:00,054 --> 00:57:01,956
No?
No.

1047
00:57:01,989 --> 00:57:04,926
You ain't the only friend
I got in the department.

1048
00:57:04,959 --> 00:57:07,628
So, tell you what.
You do this for me, and, uh...

1049
00:57:07,662 --> 00:57:08,696
Fuck off.

1050
00:57:08,729 --> 00:57:11,032
Oh, "fuck off."

1051
00:57:11,065 --> 00:57:12,566
Yeah.
That's a no too, right?

1052
00:57:14,268 --> 00:57:16,037
Walk me through that line,
Detective.

1053
00:57:16,070 --> 00:57:18,072
I said no.
No.

1054
00:57:18,105 --> 00:57:20,207
You don't get to say no.

1055
00:57:20,241 --> 00:57:22,576
You seem to have forgotten
a phone call we had earlier,

1056
00:57:22,610 --> 00:57:23,911
so let me remind you.

1057
00:57:24,946 --> 00:57:27,949
<i>Fitz, God bless him, is alive,</i>

1058
00:57:27,982 --> 00:57:29,884
<i>but only as long as I allow.</i>

1059
00:57:31,085 --> 00:57:33,220
<i>You shouldn't have come back,
Detective.</i>

1060
00:57:33,254 --> 00:57:36,123
<i>But since you're here,
I'm calling in that favor.</i>

1061
00:57:37,058 --> 00:57:38,726
[phone ringing]

1062
00:57:42,897 --> 00:57:44,632
[camera shutter clicks]
Now walk.

1063
00:57:47,835 --> 00:57:49,637
Let's go.

1064
00:57:52,239 --> 00:57:53,708
[Knight] He's clear.

1065
00:57:55,109 --> 00:57:56,744
After you.

1066
00:58:01,983 --> 00:58:03,584
[elevator bell dings]

1067
00:58:09,957 --> 00:58:11,525
[elevator bell dings]

1068
00:58:12,693 --> 00:58:14,028
What the hell
just happened here?

1069
00:58:14,061 --> 00:58:15,529
Did you search him?

1070
00:58:15,563 --> 00:58:17,665
S-So you just let him go?
Just like that?

1071
00:58:17,698 --> 00:58:19,000
You know what?

1072
00:58:19,867 --> 00:58:21,802
Something is going on there.

1073
00:58:21,836 --> 00:58:23,971
- He's got something on you.
- On me?

1074
00:58:24,005 --> 00:58:26,607
You're a fucking disgrace now.
You don't deserve this badge.

1075
00:58:26,640 --> 00:58:28,209
I'm going to report you.

1076
00:58:33,114 --> 00:58:35,116
[train horn blaring]

1077
00:58:51,632 --> 00:58:52,800
[Casey] You're fine.

1078
00:58:58,105 --> 00:59:00,741
Fuck, man.
We gotta go back and get her.

1079
00:59:01,742 --> 00:59:03,344
I'm gonna call Winna.
Okay?

1080
00:59:03,377 --> 00:59:05,312
He's got cops in his pockets.
He'll know what to do.

1081
00:59:05,346 --> 00:59:07,815
Winna only cares about himself.
He doesn't give a fuck about us.

1082
00:59:07,848 --> 00:59:10,951
Exactly. What's good for
us is good for everybody.

1083
00:59:10,985 --> 00:59:14,789
Sykes isn't gonna give us up.
Hey, you know that. Right?

1084
00:59:14,822 --> 00:59:17,792
It's in everybody's best
interest to get her free.

1085
00:59:17,825 --> 00:59:21,228
Now, flip the plates, burn everything,
stick to the fucking plan, baby.

1086
00:59:21,262 --> 00:59:22,863
Let's go. You got it.

1087
00:59:28,302 --> 00:59:31,038
[exhales] [Winna] <i>Hey, Casey,
my friend. How you doing?</i>

1088
00:59:31,072 --> 00:59:33,174
Hey, before you say anything,
no, okay?

1089
00:59:33,207 --> 00:59:34,742
Sykes isn't gonna give us up.

1090
00:59:34,775 --> 00:59:36,844
<i>Are you sure about that?</i>

1091
00:59:36,877 --> 00:59:38,345
The fuck is that
supposed to mean?

1092
00:59:38,379 --> 00:59:40,781
<i>It means I got people
in the system.</i> Yeah.

1093
00:59:40,815 --> 00:59:43,918
<i>Don't ask. If you think she's
gonna be a problem, just say so.</i>

1094
00:59:43,951 --> 00:59:45,352
<i>I can make it so she ain't.</i>

1095
00:59:46,120 --> 00:59:48,856
No, no, okay?
She's part of the team.

1096
00:59:48,889 --> 00:59:50,758
<i>Look, okay, I get it.
You're right. Fine.</i>

1097
00:59:50,791 --> 00:59:52,359
<i>Just forget anything I said,
all right?</i>

1098
00:59:52,393 --> 00:59:55,729
<i>Listen, good news,
we got the card.</i>

1099
00:59:55,763 --> 00:59:58,732
<i>But bad news is, well,
Sykes handed it off to me,</i>

1100
00:59:58,766 --> 01:00:00,801
<i>which was smart in the moment.</i>

1101
01:00:00,835 --> 01:00:03,637
<i>But to get out myself, I kind
of had to pass it off to a cop.</i>

1102
01:00:03,671 --> 01:00:05,840
<i>And now, I have no idea
where this cop is.</i>

1103
01:00:05,873 --> 01:00:08,843
<i>But don't worry about that.
All is well. All will be well.</i>

1104
01:00:08,876 --> 01:00:11,312
<i>We'll just track him down
and we'll get the card.</i>

1105
01:00:11,345 --> 01:00:13,013
Hello?

1106
01:00:13,047 --> 01:00:15,082
[Winna] <i>We are going
to be rich, my friend.</i>

1107
01:00:15,116 --> 01:00:18,419
<i>I told you, I got your back.
You have nothing to worry about.</i>

1108
01:00:18,452 --> 01:00:21,856
<i>Life is good. We're on top of
the world. I will speak to you soon.</i>

1109
01:00:22,356 --> 01:00:23,390
Hello?

1110
01:00:25,960 --> 01:00:28,329
All right. Sounds good.

1111
01:00:28,362 --> 01:00:29,997
[line clicks]
[exhales]

1112
01:00:31,132 --> 01:00:32,166
Ho!

1113
01:00:34,401 --> 01:00:35,636
Hey, Mike!

1114
01:00:38,139 --> 01:00:39,173
[laughs]

1115
01:00:41,842 --> 01:00:42,910
Whoo!

1116
01:00:43,811 --> 01:00:45,713
[gunshot]

1117
01:00:45,746 --> 01:00:47,448
Yo, Mike.
[gunfire]

1118
01:00:47,481 --> 01:00:48,716
What the fuck is that?

1119
01:00:52,486 --> 01:00:53,888
[Mike] Case!

1120
01:00:54,955 --> 01:00:55,890
Fuck!

1121
01:00:59,093 --> 01:01:00,194
[groans]

1122
01:01:06,200 --> 01:01:07,368
[glass shattering]

1123
01:01:17,077 --> 01:01:18,078
Fuck.

1124
01:01:34,295 --> 01:01:35,763
Uh-uh.

1125
01:01:35,796 --> 01:01:36,830
[grunts]
[screams]

1126
01:01:36,864 --> 01:01:38,165
[both grunting]

1127
01:01:55,482 --> 01:01:56,417
[screams]

1128
01:02:03,791 --> 01:02:05,492
[straining]

1129
01:02:06,160 --> 01:02:07,294
Die!

1130
01:02:16,337 --> 01:02:18,405
[exhales]

1131
01:02:18,439 --> 01:02:20,474
[panting]

1132
01:02:32,453 --> 01:02:34,421
[gun clicking]
[breathing heavily]

1133
01:02:34,455 --> 01:02:38,092
Okay, you're out of ammo.
This should be some fun.

1134
01:02:38,125 --> 01:02:39,493
[device beeps]

1135
01:02:44,599 --> 01:02:45,966
Hey, Mike!

1136
01:02:47,234 --> 01:02:49,370
Mike!
[groans]

1137
01:02:52,973 --> 01:02:54,241
You all right, buddy?

1138
01:02:56,511 --> 01:02:59,346
You fucking piece of shit.

1139
01:03:02,950 --> 01:03:04,151
Yo, I know this guy.

1140
01:03:06,854 --> 01:03:08,355
He's security for Winna.

1141
01:03:10,157 --> 01:03:11,225
Yo, Mikey?

1142
01:03:16,330 --> 01:03:17,364
You okay?

1143
01:03:18,165 --> 01:03:20,100
I'll get you to the hospital,
all right?

1144
01:03:20,134 --> 01:03:21,368
Okay, Mikey, look.

1145
01:03:22,637 --> 01:03:24,004
Hey, Mikey.

1146
01:03:24,639 --> 01:03:26,373
Hey, Mike! Mike!

1147
01:03:27,107 --> 01:03:29,009
Hey, buddy, you're okay.
You're okay.

1148
01:03:29,043 --> 01:03:32,079
Hey, look at me. Look at me.
You're all right, buddy.

1149
01:03:32,112 --> 01:03:35,583
We're gonna get you to the
hospital. You're gonna be all right.

1150
01:03:35,617 --> 01:03:37,084
Hey, Mikey.

1151
01:03:37,619 --> 01:03:40,220
Oh, fuck. Mike!

1152
01:03:59,306 --> 01:04:00,575
[pants]

1153
01:04:04,912 --> 01:04:06,947
[breathing heavily]

1154
01:04:08,382 --> 01:04:10,017
[engine starts]

1155
01:04:34,041 --> 01:04:35,309
[wife] <i>You think you're here?</i>

1156
01:04:44,519 --> 01:04:46,320
- [phone dialing]
- [line ringing]

1157
01:04:46,353 --> 01:04:48,322
Come on, pick up. Pick up.

1158
01:04:49,657 --> 01:04:50,692
Hi.

1159
01:04:50,725 --> 01:04:53,360
Hey, baby.
<i>Hi. Hi.</i>

1160
01:04:53,394 --> 01:04:56,631
Lily, I need you to leave the
house, get Clara and get to a hotel.

1161
01:04:56,664 --> 01:04:58,566
<i>What? What is... What...</i>

1162
01:04:58,600 --> 01:05:00,968
<i>Casey, what are you talking about?</i>
Something fucked-up happened.

1163
01:05:01,001 --> 01:05:03,170
<i>What did you do?</i>
No, no, no, no. No, no, no.

1164
01:05:03,203 --> 01:05:05,339
Hey, I need you to leave
the house right now, okay?

1165
01:05:05,372 --> 01:05:07,474
<i>What did you do, Casey?</i>
I don't have time to explain.

1166
01:05:07,509 --> 01:05:09,376
Just leave the house.
<i>Jesus! I can't believe it.</i>

1167
01:05:09,410 --> 01:05:11,311
<i>Did you hurt someone?</i>
No, it's not that.

1168
01:05:11,345 --> 01:05:14,682
Leave the house, Lily! Go!

1169
01:05:15,683 --> 01:05:17,050
[call ends]
Hell...

1170
01:05:19,453 --> 01:05:20,588
[fist thuds]
God!

1171
01:05:21,321 --> 01:05:23,390
Fuck. Fuck.

1172
01:05:28,195 --> 01:05:29,997
[line ringing]

1173
01:05:31,064 --> 01:05:32,634
[line clicks]
Mercer.

1174
01:05:32,667 --> 01:05:36,203
It's Rhodes. I need to meet.

1175
01:05:38,005 --> 01:05:39,440
[people chattering]

1176
01:05:40,107 --> 01:05:41,475
[knock on door]

1177
01:05:41,509 --> 01:05:42,943
We need to talk.

1178
01:05:52,085 --> 01:05:53,287
[door closes]

1179
01:05:54,789 --> 01:05:57,991
So, from the top.
Is Knight dirty?

1180
01:05:58,025 --> 01:06:00,194
[sighs]
I don't know. Maybe.

1181
01:06:00,227 --> 01:06:03,230
We think Winna's involved
in these heists?

1182
01:06:03,263 --> 01:06:05,600
Well, it's not a coincidence
that he was there.

1183
01:06:05,633 --> 01:06:06,701
[sighs]

1184
01:06:08,101 --> 01:06:10,505
How many cases has Knight
tanked for Winna?

1185
01:06:13,073 --> 01:06:14,676
Honestly, none.

1186
01:06:15,409 --> 01:06:16,443
[chuckles]

1187
01:06:16,477 --> 01:06:18,580
I think it was just a case of

1188
01:06:18,613 --> 01:06:20,782
"Looking the other way"
situation, you know?

1189
01:06:20,815 --> 01:06:24,719
But Knight doesn't let
anything slide, ever.

1190
01:06:24,752 --> 01:06:26,487
He's too proud.

1191
01:06:31,291 --> 01:06:32,326
Fitzgerald.

1192
01:06:32,794 --> 01:06:34,027
Who?

1193
01:06:35,496 --> 01:06:38,633
His partner. The one
who got shot by Rhodes.

1194
01:06:39,667 --> 01:06:42,604
Bet you Winna
threatened his life.

1195
01:06:42,637 --> 01:06:44,304
That explains it.

1196
01:06:44,338 --> 01:06:46,641
A bad guy said
he'd hurt his friend?

1197
01:06:46,674 --> 01:06:48,543
He is a cop.

1198
01:06:48,576 --> 01:06:51,278
He knows better than to let a
perp leave the scene of a heist.

1199
01:06:51,311 --> 01:06:53,213
And not just any perp.

1200
01:06:53,247 --> 01:06:57,417
FBI, CIA, ATF
all have open cases on Winna.

1201
01:06:57,451 --> 01:06:59,721
He's a slimy, rich
asshole bastard.

1202
01:06:59,754 --> 01:07:03,056
He's been sliding out of each and every
investigation, throwing his money around.

1203
01:07:03,090 --> 01:07:05,560
He is the cause of
what's wrong with this city.

1204
01:07:05,593 --> 01:07:09,631
He even used to be a CI and
played the force to eliminate his rivals.

1205
01:07:09,664 --> 01:07:11,365
You think we don't know
about Winna?

1206
01:07:11,398 --> 01:07:13,066
We have been on his ass
for years!

1207
01:07:13,100 --> 01:07:15,469
And two city cops from LA
walk in here

1208
01:07:15,503 --> 01:07:17,237
and think they're
gonna handle this shit,

1209
01:07:17,271 --> 01:07:19,239
fuckin' up
the whole entire case?

1210
01:07:20,508 --> 01:07:22,577
The woman, she said something?

1211
01:07:23,711 --> 01:07:25,680
Not a word.
Listen.

1212
01:07:27,615 --> 01:07:30,083
I can get her to speak.
Give me five minutes.

1213
01:07:30,117 --> 01:07:32,820
Be lucky you are not
in the cell next to her.

1214
01:07:32,854 --> 01:07:36,390
Knight goes anywhere
near this case or Winna,

1215
01:07:36,423 --> 01:07:38,292
I will have him
in a cell so long

1216
01:07:38,325 --> 01:07:40,160
it will rot
his fucking head off.

1217
01:07:42,564 --> 01:07:43,698
Get out of my office.

1218
01:07:46,166 --> 01:07:48,068
[exhales]

1219
01:07:49,571 --> 01:07:51,204
[San go sighs]

1220
01:08:00,548 --> 01:08:02,082
[horn honks]

1221
01:08:03,851 --> 01:08:05,520
[glasses clinking]

1222
01:08:05,553 --> 01:08:07,220
[people chattering]

1223
01:08:09,524 --> 01:08:12,359
[San go] <i>You're a fucking disgrace
now. You don't deserve this badge.</i>

1224
01:08:13,828 --> 01:08:17,431
<i>Something is going on there.
He's got something on you.</i>

1225
01:08:20,467 --> 01:08:22,102
[no audible dialogue]

1226
01:08:44,391 --> 01:08:45,492
[gunshot]

1227
01:08:54,401 --> 01:08:55,703
[gunshot]

1228
01:09:35,810 --> 01:09:37,845
[phone ringing]

1229
01:09:41,949 --> 01:09:43,651
[ringing continues]

1230
01:09:49,023 --> 01:09:50,490
[beeps]

1231
01:09:53,995 --> 01:09:56,631
<i>Hey, it's your favorite CI
Winna.</i>

1232
01:09:56,664 --> 01:09:59,433
<i>Just letting you know, Leach
will be coming by any second.</i>

1233
01:09:59,466 --> 01:10:02,637
<i>And, uh, don't forget,
Detective, you owe me.</i>

1234
01:10:17,919 --> 01:10:18,953
[body thuds]

1235
01:10:20,621 --> 01:10:21,756
[exhales]

1236
01:10:21,789 --> 01:10:23,591
[phone ringing]
[phone vibrating]

1237
01:10:26,627 --> 01:10:30,363
[vibrating continues]
[ringing fades]

1238
01:10:33,000 --> 01:10:34,836
[Winna]
<i>How's my favorite detective?</i>

1239
01:10:34,869 --> 01:10:36,671
Yeah, what's it to you?

1240
01:10:36,704 --> 01:10:39,439
Oh, let's meet.

1241
01:10:39,473 --> 01:10:41,542
I think we should meet.

1242
01:10:44,377 --> 01:10:46,413
- [phone beeps]
- [line clicks]

1243
01:10:53,788 --> 01:10:55,455
[exhales, sniffs]

1244
01:11:17,678 --> 01:11:19,714
[breathing heavily]

1245
01:11:25,920 --> 01:11:27,555
[typing on phone]

